In a World Like This is the eighth studio album (seventh in the U.S.) by the Backstreet Boys, released on July 30, 2013. It's a follow-up to 2009's This Is Us. It's the first album featuring all five original members in six years since Kevin Richardson left the group in 2006 to focus on his family and pursue other interests. Richardson rejoined the group in 2012. It will also be their first independent album after they left their old label Jive Records in 2010.

On May 20, 2013, the group released &quot;Permanent Stain&quot; as a promotional single, which was co-written by band member Nick Carter. A free download of the song was offered with the purchase of a ticket for their In a World Like This Tour. The first single from the album, also titled &quot;In a World Like This&quot; premiered on Z100 New York on June 18, 2013 and was released on June 25, 2013.

